<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 02 at 10:40AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT AS SNOW INCREASES
INTENSITY DURING LATE MORNING INTO EARLY AFTERNOON...
WEATHER...
* Snow moving in from northern Indiana brings increased intensity during
late morning into early afternoon.
* Additional accumulation up to 1 inch near the Ohio border and 1
to 2 inches north of I-94 between 1030 AM and 100 PM.
* Temperatures fall into the 20s during the afternoon.
IMPACTS...
* Driving conditions become increasingly hazardous due to low
visibility and worsening road conditions.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for the
hazardous driving conditions by allowing extra time.
* Reduced travel speed will be required as wet roads become
slushy and snow covered.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
